  "text": "For the ship tracking, the dynamic model is given in [CITATION_1] . All the density distributions are Gaussian so we can analytically obtain some function values. Equation (5) linearizes the last equation of (1). Thus, the dynamic model becomes the one with linear Gaussian state space. This model actually is not Markovian as (5) depends on and . We can choose the optimal function , since particles can be sampled from directly. Thus, the importance weight function (23) becomes (28) We already derived the posterior density distribution function for components and in (8), (9), (10), and [CITATION_2] .",
